y the degree to which parameters can be constrained with the obtained\nphotometry. We find that, while ultra-violet data alone constrains parameters\ngoverning the outer ejecta properties, the combination of both ground-based\noptical and space-based ultra-violet data allows for tight constraints for all\nbut one parameter of the kilonova model up to 160 Mpc. These results imply that\nan ultra-violet mission like Dorado would provide unique insights into the\nearly evolution of the post-merger system and its driving emission physics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Jun 2022 10:34:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-22"}
